10 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to establish a
11 housing infrastructure tax increment financing program, administered by the
12 Vermont Economic Progress Council, to authorize municipalities to use
13 statewide education property tax and municipal property tax increment to pay
14 for financing undertaken by the municipality, a developer, or a sponsor for
15 infrastructure that will stimulate housing development within a geographically
16 eligible area.
17 An act relating to tax increment financing for housing infrastructure
18 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
19 Sec. 1. 24 V.S.A. chapter 53, subchapter 7 is added to read:
