13 § 1910b. USE OF TAX INCREMENT; RETENTION PERIOD;
14 SUBSTANTIAL COMPLETION
15 (a) Education property tax increment. For only debt incurred within the
16 period permitted under subsection 1910(a) of this subchapter and related costs,
17 up to 80 percent of the education property tax increment may be retained for
18 up to 20 years, beginning on July 1 of the year in which the Vermont
19 Economic Progress Council certifies substantial completion of the housing
20 development pursuant to subsection (d) of this section.
